# Committed, non-secret build flags. `.env.local` (gitignored) overrides these.

# Use React Native's own fetch instead of `expo/fetch`.
#
# `expo/src/winter/runtime.native.ts` throws at startup if `globalThis.Headers`
# is missing:
#
#   expo/fetch expected `globalThis.Headers` to be installed by React Native's
#   fetch polyfill.
#
# Whether it is missing depends on module ordering. An EAS Build bundle
# (`expo export:embed`) carries `getModulesRunBeforeMainModule`, so RN's core is
# initialized first and the polyfill is there. An OTA bundle (`expo export`,
# which is what `eas update` publishes) does not — Expo's own source comments
# that this metadata "is unstable or can be missing". So expo/fetch throws
# during startup, the update crashes before React renders, expo-updates rolls
# back to the embedded bundle, and the update is marked failed.
#
# That is the entire reason OTA updates never worked here: the embedded bundle
# was always fine, and every published update was dead on arrival.
#
# Expo provides this flag as the escape hatch. RN's fetch is all Convex and
# expo-auth-session need, so there is nothing to lose by using it.
EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_RN_FETCH=1
